title: Couple Rearranged Things.
message:
Couple Rearranged Things.

IFormatReader changed to static class IFormat with an interface in it called Reader. getReaderByExtention() got moved into there. And replaced the cascading checks with a switch statement StitchType got put into IFormat. Updated PointList moved the one segment bit into StitchBlock. Checks whether single remove changes the bounds, and includes some other bounds operations. Stopped Crashing of Improper Format. And fixed Manifest to not try those (most of the time).

title: Core Fix, Massive Speed Increase.
message:
Core Fix, Massive Speed Increase.

Releasing my PointList class. I improve the draw speed significantly of the core type, allowing the project to ultimately be successful. Without this change Android would not be able to rerender fast enough to draw much of anything. I also added in a basic form of how the Matrix for view and Touch work. Also a core touch event, that simply adds lines.
